  "prompt": "Why are so many questions are asked anonymously in Quora nowadays?",
  "response": "There could be several reasons why people ask questions anonymously on Quora:\n\n1. Privacy concerns\n- Sensitive or personal topics\n- Fear of judgment\n- Protecting personal identity\n\n2. Professional reasons\n- Asking about workplace issues\n- Career-related sensitive questions\n- Avoiding potential professional repercussions\n\n3. Embarrassment\n- Discussing personal health issues\n- Relationship problems\n- Intimate or awkward subjects\n\n4. Controversial topics\n- Political opinions\n- Religious discussions\n- Potentially polarizing subjects\n\n5. Personal insecurity\n- Low self-confidence\n- Fear of criticism\n- Avoiding potential online harassment\n\n6. Protection from social media consequences\n- Preventing potential backlash\n- Maintaining a clean public image\n\n7. Cultural or social constraints\n- Discussing topics considered taboo\n- Avoiding social stigma\n- Protecting family reputation\n\n8. Technical convenience\n- Easy anonymous option on platform\n- Minimal effort to ask questions\n\nThese factors contribute to the increasing trend of anonymous questioning on platforms like Quora, where users seek information while maintaining personal anonymity.",
